title: Ten Airports I've Visited
name: Ten Airports I've Visited
description:
A Map by Flyboy18

These are ten airports I've landed at either during my flight training or after I've gotten my pilot's license.

properties.name: Collegedale Municipal Airport
properties.description: Posted by Flyboy18I flew down here during Christmas break to pick up my roommate. I flew him around the local area and even let him take the controls for a little while. He had a really good time. I did have a little trouble locating the airport when I was ready to land because the terrain obscures it until you\'re right on top of it. I eventually found it and we got on the ground just fine.

properties.name: Crossville Municipal Airport
properties.description: Posted by Flyboy18I did some training here, but I\'ve also visited it a few times since I\'ve had my license.

properties.name: Lebanon Municipal Airport
properties.description: Posted by Flyboy18This is currently my home base. I\'ve been flying here for a little over a year now. It\'s pretty cool to land here because you have to fly right over the interstate to get to the runway.

properties.name: McGhee-Tyson Airport
properties.description: Posted by Flyboy18I flew here to practice working with the air traffic controllers. It was awesome getting to talk to them over the radio. I felt like a big time pilot.

properties.name: Scott Municipal Airport
properties.description: Posted by Flyboy18My dad and I made a trip up here last summer. It was really pretty getting to fly over the Big South Fork National Park, but it was really bumpy that day. I don\'t think my dad enjoyed it as much as I did, but it was still a lot of fun.

properties.name: Smyrna Airport
properties.description: Posted by Flyboy18I flew here to once again practice working with the air traffic controllers. It was different here because, unlike at McGhee-Tyson, I didn\'t have my instructor with me. It was just a really cool experience.

properties.name: Upper Cumberland Regional Airport
properties.description: Posted by Flyboy18Most of my flight training took place here.

properties.name: Warren County Memorial Airport
properties.description: Posted by Flyboy18I had to fly here from Sparta to take my checkride with the flight examiner. Whether you pass or fail the checkride determines whether or not you get your license. I was so excited when the examiner asked me who my first passengers were going to be. It was awesome!

properties.name: Warren County Regional Airport
properties.description: Posted by Flyboy18I flew here along with my dad and instructor to practice navigation. It was a really fun trip.

properties.name: Wayne County Municipal Airport
properties.description: Posted by Flyboy18I flew up here for my first solo cross country flight. It was a little scary being alone on a long flight for the first time, but I did it. I felt a really big sense of accomplishment afterwards.
